 DURING LANDING ROLL, THE PILOT INADVERTENTLY ENTERED A GROUND LOOP.  
WHEN HE ATTEMPTED RUDDER INPUT TO CORRECT FOR THE GROUND LOOP, THE 
RUDDER CONTROL MIXING UNIT IN THE EMPENNAGE SHIFTED AND JAMMED THE 
RUDDER. CONTINUED PRESSURE ON THE RUDDER PEDALS BY THE PILOT 
FRACTURED THE LEFT RUDDER PEDAL AT THE CROSSOVER BAR.  THE AIRCRAFT 
WING STRUCK THE GROUND DURING THE EVOLUTION CAUSING SUBSTANTIAL 
DAMAGE TO THE LEFT WING. 
 A FAILURE OF THE RUDDER CONTROL SYSTEM WHEN THE PILOT ATTEMPTED TO 
CORRECT FOR AN INADVERTENT GROUND LOOP DURING LANDING ROLL. 
